cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with privacy-preserving mechanisms and incentive-compatible mechanisms, which are topics commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and game theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. The paper also involves statistical modeling and estimation, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a Bayesian mechanism, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
